ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is pretty different from most physics courses, but not in a bad way. Rather than focusing on learning formulas and applying mathematics, the course tries to give students a conceptual overview to gain an understanding of the foundations of nuclear physics and current experimental work in the subject. I would recommend it; you'll learn a lot, and if you're even considering nuclear physics, or just interested in it, you would gain a lot from it.
I would recommend this course to any studetwo was going to work in nuclear or astrophysics.
